{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "foundation_knowledge", "content": "# A.I.M. Technical Specification\n\nThis document provides the literal, metaphor-free engineering specifications for the A.I.M. OS.\n\n## 1. Database Schema (`engram.db`)\nThe core memory layer is a local SQLite database utilizing parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection. It implements Hybrid Retrieval (Semantic Cosine Similarity + FTS5 BM25).\n\n### `sessions` Table\nTracks ingestion sources and provides chronological metadata.\n*   `id` (TEXT PRIMARY KEY)\n*   `filename` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n*   `mtime` (REAL NOT NULL)\n*   `indexed_at` (TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)\n\n### `fragments` Table\nStores the actual semantic chunks.\n*   `id` (INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT)\n*   `session_id` (TEXT NOT NULL) - Foreign Key to `sessions(id)` ON DELETE CASCADE\n*   `type` (TEXT NOT NULL) - e.g., 'foundation_knowledge', 'expert_knowledge', 'user_prompt', 'model_response'\n*   `content` (TEXT NOT NULL)\n*   `timestamp` (TEXT)\n*   `embedding` (BLOB) - 768-dimensional float array packed via `struct` (Nomic standard).\n*   `metadata` (TEXT) - JSON string containing tool call arguments or routing data.\n\n### `fragments_fts` (Virtual Table)\nAn FTS5 virtual table synchronized via 3 SQLite triggers (`AFTER INSERT`, `AFTER DELETE`, `AFTER UPDATE`) on the `fragments` table to provide zero-latency exact-match keyword search (BM25 algorithm).\n\n## 2. Token Economics & Benchmarks\nThe distillation pipeline operates to drastically reduce token payload before semantic embedding. \n\n### Empirical Methodology\nThe `extract_signal.py` script targets massive raw JSON session files generated by the CLI. It physically strips out all ANSI color codes, verbatim `stdout` dumps, and system metadata, leaving only the \"Signal Skeleton\" (Intents, Tool Calls, and Outcome Booleans). \n\n### Variance Data (Real-World Samples)\nCompression ratios vary based on the ratio of \"terminal noise\" to \"architectural logic\" in a given session.\n*   **Sample A (Heavy Terminal Execution - 50+ Turns):**\n    *   *Raw Payload:* 8.76 MB\n ", "timestamp": "2026-03-28T02:41:22.202426", "embedding": [0.4393291771411896, 1.7013113498687744, -2.602132797241211, -2.1662979125976562, 1.1345685720443726, -1.5038552284240723, 0.48473304510116577, 0.7808670401573181, -0.5212963819503784, -0.6069808006286621, -0.26332324743270874, 0.62217777967453, 1.204500436782837, -0.1299571543931961, 0.04630940034985542, -0.38178056478500366, -0.7218422293663025, -0.3097667396068573, -0.2835853397846222, 0.7700873613357544, -0.19163712859153748, 0.24916040897369385, -0.5418825149536133, -1.167842149734497, 1.6695982217788696, 1.159004807472229, -0.6803386807441711, -0.04949819669127464, -0.1732187569141388, 0.0656612291932106, 0.7001640200614929, -0.21188296377658844, -0.23801223933696747, -0.10023151338100433, -1.567311406135559, -1.7135250568389893, -0.028534049168229103, 0.032915037125349045, 0.282140851020813, 0.12284822762012482, 0.4332544505596161, 0.3665318191051483, -0.16312356293201447, -0.5751619935035706, 0.03356750309467316, 0.7140516042709351, 0.9593521952629089, -0.048103783279657364, 1.1784566640853882, -1.8340553045272827, 0.14005859196186066, 0.13601462543010712, 0.8540334701538086, -0.8984525799751282, 1.1220417022705078, 0.47980210185050964, 0.20235873758792877, 0.8833403587341309, -0.1800750195980072, -0.5417797565460205, 1.0048410892486572, 1.0022772550582886, -1.367023229598999, 1.2690620422363281, 0.06892868131399155, 0.22407934069633484, -0.6831538677215576, 0.5386345982551575, 0.5354365110397339, -0.6244373321533203, 1.217954158782959, 0.23243682086467743, -1.0076466798782349, 0.6068632006645203, 0.033586472272872925, 0.19872622191905975, -0.39746102690696716, -0.14250728487968445, 0.13764771819114685, 0.7808405160903931, 0.2631681263446808, 0.26000285148620605, 1.945185661315918, -0.5542675256729126, 0.8073441982269287, 0.5064361095428467, -0.9380953311920166, 0.07449457794427872, 0.1